  "body": "Currently `core.go` holds beacon chain database, state snapshots, a lock and many more methods. Some of those methods can be converted to be stateless and some methods really belong in types (which is what the state package is called) and casper package. There's some overlap and we could find a better way to organize `block chain`, `casper` and `types` packages better.\r\n\r\nThis issue addresses how to clearly defining each package as well as refactoring them.\r\n",
