    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "With the recent refactor (https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/commit/f312c013fcc677c1fdc29a36ff03e93a1367db0d), a lot of `core.go` code got moved over to `block.go`, `active_state.go`, and `crystallized_state.go`. I'm going to start working on migrating over to Bolt, which will move the rest of the database logic into its own package as well. \r\n\r\nI think the distinction between `types` and `casper` is a little blurry, since they both contain logic that's related to Casper somewhat. `types` imports `casper` but not the other way around, and `casper` deals strictly with protobuf messages when handling state. \r\n\r\nWould be nice to better organize these packages. Otherwise, we could just close this?",
